<doc id="539021" wikidata="Q5325323" url="?curid=539021" title="Eaglecrest Ski Area">
<text>Eaglecrest Ski Area is a public ski area on Douglas Island in the U.S. state of Alaska, across Gastineau Channel from Juneau. The area is owned and operated by Juneau&#x27;s municipal government. Eaglecrest has 4 double chairlifts accessing , with 36 marked alpine runs, two Nordic skiing loops, and access to world class backcountry. Vertical drop is with an average snowfall of 320&quot; and a record snowfall of 640&quot; in 2011.

Southeast Alaska&#x27;s only ski area, Eaglecrest&#x27;s season generally runs from the first weekend of December through mid-April.

Eaglecrest is family and community-oriented, with many community outreach programs available, including a snowsports school offering lessons to students with physical and learning disabilities.

Eaglecrest now has 36 official alpine runs to go with East &amp; West Bowls, Pittman&#x27;s Ridge, Hilda &amp; Benches Glades, and 8 km of Nordic trails. When snow and staffing allows, the mountain also offers a Terrain Park.

