<doc id="539115" wikidata="Q5376722" url="?curid=539115" title="Enebyberg">
<text>Enebyberg is a suburban area in Stockholm, Sweden and a part of Danderyd Municipality, Stockholm County. It was founded in the beginning of the 1900s and became a municipal community in 1914. Enebyberg later merged with Danderyd, Stocksund, and Djursholm to form Danderyd Municipality. Its location is very close to Täby Municipality, therefore forming a part of its urban area. Swedish writer Jonas Gardell is from Enebyberg.</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q1754" start="32" end="41" title="Stockholm" label="Stockholm"/>
<link wikidata="Q34" start="43" end="49" title="Sweden" label="Sweden"/>
<link wikidata="Q113679" start="64" end="85" title="Danderyd Municipality" label="Danderyd Municipality"/>
<link wikidata="Q104231" start="87" end="103" title="Stockholm County" label="Stockholm County"/>
<link wikidata="Q5215713" start="220" end="228" title="Danderyd Ship District" label="Danderyd"/>
<link wikidata="Q2943721" start="230" end="239" title="Stocksund" label="Stocksund"/>
<link wikidata="Q990076" start="245" end="254" title="Djursholm" label="Djursholm"/>
<link wikidata="Q493066" start="316" end="333" title="Täby Municipality" label="Täby Municipality"/>
<link wikidata="Q982351" start="394" end="407" title="Jonas Gardell" label="Jonas Gardell"/>
</links>
